[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":746},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife\u002F":721,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F20\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife\u002F":730},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190520\u002F1388644925\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":704,"date":705,"description":706,"extension":707,"lang":708,"meta":709,"navigation":96,"path":710,"readingMinutes":711,"seo":712,"standalone":713,"stem":714,"tags":715,"tldr":718,"updated":705,"url":719,"__hash__":720},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-36-iife.md","[JS Weird World] No.36 Immediately Invoked Function Expressions (IIFEs)","1000229654",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":698},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,32,40,107,110,152,156,167,202,205,256,263,266,269,382,388,391,394,436,442,445,448,481,484,490,497,500,536,539,545,548,588,594,597,675,681,685,694],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"An Immediately Invoked Function Expression — IIFE for short — is something a lot of people have already bumped into. But what actually ",[21,22,23],"em",{},"is"," an IIFE? How does it work, and what's it good for? That's what we're digging into in this chapter.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"function-statements-vs-function-expressions","Function Statements vs Function Expressions",[17,30,31],{},"First off, we already know the difference between a function statement and a function expression.",[17,33,34,35,39],{},"This is a function statement. After JavaScript runs through it, it just sits in memory — it won't actually execute unless we call ",[36,37,38],"code",{},"greet()",".",[41,42,47],"pre",{"className":43,"code":44,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","function greet() {\n  console.log('Hello');\n}\n\ngreet();\n","js","",[36,48,49,66,85,91,98],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,51,54,58,62],"span",{"class":52,"line":53},"line",1,[50,55,57],{"class":56},"sWyjQ","function",[50,59,61],{"class":60},"sj_SG"," greet",[50,63,65],{"class":64},"sMAXC","() {\n",[50,67,69,72,75,78,82],{"class":52,"line":68},2,[50,70,71],{"class":64},"  console.",[50,73,74],{"class":60},"log",[50,76,77],{"class":64},"(",[50,79,81],{"class":80},"sTRMh","'Hello'",[50,83,84],{"class":64},");\n",[50,86,88],{"class":52,"line":87},3,[50,89,90],{"class":64},"}\n",[50,92,94],{"class":52,"line":93},4,[50,95,97],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":96},true,"\n",[50,99,101,104],{"class":52,"line":100},5,[50,102,103],{"class":60},"greet",[50,105,106],{"class":64},"();\n",[17,108,109],{},"A function expression looks like this. It isn't stored in memory at the start — only the variable gets stored, because variables get hoisted. The moment JavaScript hits this line, it creates the execution context right then. That's a function expression.",[41,111,113],{"className":43,"code":112,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"var greetFunction = function() {\n  ...\n};\n\ngreetFunction();\n",[36,114,115,131,136,141,145],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,116,117,120,123,126,129],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,118,119],{"class":56},"var",[50,121,122],{"class":60}," greetFunction",[50,124,125],{"class":56}," =",[50,127,128],{"class":56}," function",[50,130,65],{"class":64},[50,132,133],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,134,135],{"class":56},"  ...\n",[50,137,138],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,139,140],{"class":64},"};\n",[50,142,143],{"class":52,"line":93},[50,144,97],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":96},[50,146,147,150],{"class":52,"line":100},[50,148,149],{"class":60},"greetFunction",[50,151,106],{"class":64},[12,153,155],{"id":154},"iife","IIFE",[17,157,158,159,162,163,166],{},"OK, quick recap done. Now we can do something a little special with a function and turn it into a special object. What if we want to call a function expression ",[21,160,161],{},"immediately",", instead of going through ",[36,164,165],{},"greetFunction();","?",[41,168,170],{"className":43,"code":169,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"var greetFunction = function() {\n  console.log('Hi');\n}();\n",[36,171,172,184,197],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,173,174,176,178,180,182],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,175,119],{"class":56},[50,177,122],{"class":60},[50,179,125],{"class":56},[50,181,128],{"class":56},[50,183,65],{"class":64},[50,185,186,188,190,192,195],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,187,71],{"class":64},[50,189,74],{"class":60},[50,191,77],{"class":64},[50,193,194],{"class":80},"'Hi'",[50,196,84],{"class":64},[50,198,199],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,200,201],{"class":64},"}();\n",[17,203,204],{},"You just tack a pair of parens on the end. And if we want to pass arguments, where do they go? Same place — right inside those parens.",[41,206,208],{"className":43,"code":207,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"var greetFunction = function(name) {\n  console.log('Hi ' + name);\n}('Jack');\n",[36,209,210,229,246],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,211,212,214,216,218,220,222,226],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,213,119],{"class":56},[50,215,122],{"class":60},[50,217,125],{"class":56},[50,219,128],{"class":56},[50,221,77],{"class":64},[50,223,225],{"class":224},"s_sBn","name",[50,227,228],{"class":64},") {\n",[50,230,231,233,235,237,240,243],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,232,71],{"class":64},[50,234,74],{"class":60},[50,236,77],{"class":64},[50,238,239],{"class":80},"'Hi '",[50,241,242],{"class":56}," +",[50,244,245],{"class":64}," name);\n",[50,247,248,251,254],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,249,250],{"class":64},"}(",[50,252,253],{"class":80},"'Jack'",[50,255,84],{"class":64},[17,257,258],{},[259,260],"img",{"alt":261,"src":262},"IIFE result in the console","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FuQquou6.png",[17,264,265],{},"The idea here is that the function gets called (executed) the moment it's created. That's what people mean by an Immediately Invoked Function Expression, a.k.a. IIFE.",[17,267,268],{},"So let's look at how these two differ.",[41,270,272],{"className":43,"code":271,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"var greetFunctionTwo = function(name) {\n  console.log('Hi ' + name);\n};\nconsole.log(greetFunctionTwo);\n\n\u002F\u002F IIFE\nvar greetFunction = function(name) {\n  console.log('Hi' + name);\n}();\n\nconsole.log(greetFunction);\n",[36,273,274,291,305,309,319,323,330,347,362,367,372],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,275,276,278,281,283,285,287,289],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,277,119],{"class":56},[50,279,280],{"class":60}," greetFunctionTwo",[50,282,125],{"class":56},[50,284,128],{"class":56},[50,286,77],{"class":64},[50,288,225],{"class":224},[50,290,228],{"class":64},[50,292,293,295,297,299,301,303],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,294,71],{"class":64},[50,296,74],{"class":60},[50,298,77],{"class":64},[50,300,239],{"class":80},[50,302,242],{"class":56},[50,304,245],{"class":64},[50,306,307],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,308,140],{"class":64},[50,310,311,314,316],{"class":52,"line":93},[50,312,313],{"class":64},"console.",[50,315,74],{"class":60},[50,317,318],{"class":64},"(greetFunctionTwo);\n",[50,320,321],{"class":52,"line":100},[50,322,97],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":96},[50,324,326],{"class":52,"line":325},6,[50,327,329],{"class":328},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F IIFE\n",[50,331,333,335,337,339,341,343,345],{"class":52,"line":332},7,[50,334,119],{"class":56},[50,336,122],{"class":60},[50,338,125],{"class":56},[50,340,128],{"class":56},[50,342,77],{"class":64},[50,344,225],{"class":224},[50,346,228],{"class":64},[50,348,350,352,354,356,358,360],{"class":52,"line":349},8,[50,351,71],{"class":64},[50,353,74],{"class":60},[50,355,77],{"class":64},[50,357,194],{"class":80},[50,359,242],{"class":56},[50,361,245],{"class":64},[50,363,365],{"class":52,"line":364},9,[50,366,201],{"class":64},[50,368,370],{"class":52,"line":369},10,[50,371,97],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":96},[50,373,375,377,379],{"class":52,"line":374},11,[50,376,313],{"class":64},[50,378,74],{"class":60},[50,380,381],{"class":64},"(greetFunction);\n",[17,383,384],{},[259,385],{"alt":386,"src":387},"Comparing a function expression with an IIFE in the console","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPP8jvTk.png",[17,389,390],{},"Notice that the non-IIFE version gives you the whole function back, while the IIFE gives you a value directly. That's the difference between the two.",[17,392,393],{},"There's another way to write this, of course.",[41,395,397],{"className":43,"code":396,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"(function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name)\n})('Jack');\n",[36,398,399,411,427],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,400,401,403,405,407,409],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,402,77],{"class":64},[50,404,57],{"class":56},[50,406,77],{"class":64},[50,408,225],{"class":224},[50,410,228],{"class":64},[50,412,413,416,418,420,422,424],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,414,415],{"class":64}," console.",[50,417,74],{"class":60},[50,419,77],{"class":64},[50,421,194],{"class":80},[50,423,242],{"class":56},[50,425,426],{"class":64},"  name)\n",[50,428,429,432,434],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,430,431],{"class":64},"})(",[50,433,253],{"class":80},[50,435,84],{"class":64},[17,437,438],{},[259,439],{"alt":440,"src":441},"IIFE written with wrapping parentheses","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaURma5S.png",[17,443,444],{},"This is what people call an anonymous function — a function I can run directly without giving it a name.",[17,446,447],{},"But what about this?",[41,449,451],{"className":43,"code":450,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name)\n}\n",[36,452,453,463,477],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,454,455,457,459,461],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,456,57],{"class":56},[50,458,77],{"class":64},[50,460,225],{"class":224},[50,462,228],{"class":64},[50,464,465,467,469,471,473,475],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,466,415],{"class":64},[50,468,74],{"class":60},[50,470,77],{"class":64},[50,472,194],{"class":80},[50,474,242],{"class":56},[50,476,426],{"class":64},[50,478,479],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,480,90],{"class":64},[17,482,483],{},"You'll get an error.",[17,485,486],{},[259,487],{"alt":488,"src":489},"Syntax error from a bare anonymous function","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRMCJ23K.png",[17,491,492,493,496],{},"Here's why. When the syntax parser reads the first line and hits ",[36,494,495],{},"f-u...",", it keeps parsing and thinks, \"Oh, this is a function statement, so there should be a name coming up next.\" But we never gave the function a name, so it errors out.",[17,498,499],{},"To stop the syntax parser from treating it as a function statement, we wrap the whole thing in parens. When the parser hits the opening paren, it goes, \"Oh, this is a function expression\" — just like the earlier example.",[41,501,503],{"className":43,"code":502,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"(function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name)\n})\n",[36,504,505,517,531],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,506,507,509,511,513,515],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,508,77],{"class":64},[50,510,57],{"class":56},[50,512,77],{"class":64},[50,514,225],{"class":224},[50,516,228],{"class":64},[50,518,519,521,523,525,527,529],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,520,415],{"class":64},[50,522,74],{"class":60},[50,524,77],{"class":64},[50,526,194],{"class":80},[50,528,242],{"class":56},[50,530,426],{"class":64},[50,532,533],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,534,535],{"class":64},"})\n",[17,537,538],{},"But if you paste this in and run it, you'll see something kind of interesting.",[17,540,541],{},[259,542],{"alt":543,"src":544},"The wrapped function expression returned in the console","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmBAkYrY.png",[17,546,547],{},"It just returns a function. So to actually call it, we add parens at the end — and we can pass arguments inside those parens too.",[41,549,551],{"className":43,"code":550,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"(function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name);\n})('Jack');\n",[36,552,553,565,580],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,554,555,557,559,561,563],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,556,77],{"class":64},[50,558,57],{"class":56},[50,560,77],{"class":64},[50,562,225],{"class":224},[50,564,228],{"class":64},[50,566,567,569,571,573,575,577],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,568,415],{"class":64},[50,570,74],{"class":60},[50,572,77],{"class":64},[50,574,194],{"class":80},[50,576,242],{"class":56},[50,578,579],{"class":64},"  name);\n",[50,581,582,584,586],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,583,431],{"class":64},[50,585,253],{"class":80},[50,587,84],{"class":64},[17,589,590],{},[259,591],{"alt":592,"src":593},"Calling the IIFE with an argument","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbZ4cGVJ.png",[17,595,596],{},"One last thing the course points out: both of these IIFEs are perfectly valid and correct. It's purely a matter of taste.",[41,598,600],{"className":43,"code":599,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"(function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name);\n})('Jack');\n\n(function(name) {\n console.log('Hi' +  name);\n}('Jack'));\n",[36,601,602,614,628,636,640,652,666],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,603,604,606,608,610,612],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,605,77],{"class":64},[50,607,57],{"class":56},[50,609,77],{"class":64},[50,611,225],{"class":224},[50,613,228],{"class":64},[50,615,616,618,620,622,624,626],{"class":52,"line":68},[50,617,415],{"class":64},[50,619,74],{"class":60},[50,621,77],{"class":64},[50,623,194],{"class":80},[50,625,242],{"class":56},[50,627,579],{"class":64},[50,629,630,632,634],{"class":52,"line":87},[50,631,431],{"class":64},[50,633,253],{"class":80},[50,635,84],{"class":64},[50,637,638],{"class":52,"line":93},[50,639,97],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":96},[50,641,642,644,646,648,650],{"class":52,"line":100},[50,643,77],{"class":64},[50,645,57],{"class":56},[50,647,77],{"class":64},[50,649,225],{"class":224},[50,651,228],{"class":64},[50,653,654,656,658,660,662,664],{"class":52,"line":325},[50,655,415],{"class":64},[50,657,74],{"class":60},[50,659,77],{"class":64},[50,661,194],{"class":80},[50,663,242],{"class":56},[50,665,579],{"class":64},[50,667,668,670,672],{"class":52,"line":332},[50,669,250],{"class":64},[50,671,253],{"class":80},[50,673,674],{"class":64},"));\n",[17,676,677],{},[259,678],{"alt":679,"src":680},"Both IIFE styles are just a matter of aesthetics","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmVgJS83.png",[12,682,684],{"id":683},"image-source","Image Source",[17,686,687],{},[688,689,693],"a",{"href":690,"rel":691},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fjavascriptjs\u002F",[692],"nofollow","JavaScript 全攻略:克服 JS 奇怪的部分",[695,696,697],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}",{"title":46,"searchDepth":68,"depth":68,"links":699},[700,701,702,703],{"id":14,"depth":68,"text":15},{"id":27,"depth":68,"text":28},{"id":154,"depth":68,"text":155},{"id":683,"depth":68,"text":684},"JsWeirdWorld","2019-05-20 13:00:00","An Immediately Invoked Function Expression, or IIFE, is something a lot of people have already run into. But what actually is an IIFE? How does it work, 